  "mandatory_limitations": [
    "The target is a frozen surface-language marker in the ensuing visible completion and only an observable process-trace proxy; it is not private chain-of-thought, hidden reasoning, understanding, intent, or emotion.",
    "The intervals and tests use saved fixed out-of-fold predictions selected after point results were observed; they omit model-refit and model-or-feature-selection uncertainty.",
    "The Student-t intervals assume ten repository deltas are iid, and the exact sign-flip tests assume repository-level sign symmetry.",
    "Holm adjustment covers only the frozen family of two nested candidates by two decomposable loss metrics and does not make this analysis confirmatory or transportable."
  ]
